The paper focuses on human-robot interaction and decision-making, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study specifically investigates the perception of robots as having minds, which is related to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also explores the mechanisms of social influence, which is relevant to the field of social computing (cs.SI). Finally, the study provides insights into the dynamics of decision-making with robots, which could be relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY).
